==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tunicated
<hw>Tu"ni*ca`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>tunicatus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>tunicare</ets> to clothe with a tunic, fr. <ets>tunica</ets> a
tunic.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with a tunic;
covered or coated with layers; <as>as, a <ex>tunicated</ex>
bulb</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having a tunic, or
mantle; of or pertaining to the Tunicata.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having
each joint buried in the preceding funnel-shaped one, as in certain
antennae of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tunicate</ent>⟦br⟧
